model_patch.ohos_7zip/library/src/main/cpp/uncompres:
Looking at the code, the warning indicates that `i < offset` is always true because the loop runs from 0 to `bits-1`, and if `offset >= bits`, the condition is always true. The logic seems to be inverted - it should check if `i >= offset` to use letters, otherwise use digits.

```diff
--- a/ohos_7zip/library/src/main/cpp/uncompress/uncompress.cpp
+++ b/ohos_7zip/library/src/main/cpp/uncompress/uncompress.cpp
@@ -43,7 +43,7 @@ namespace Oh7zip {
     for (int i = 0; i < bits; i++) {
         int j = dis(generate);
-        tmp += (i < offset) ? ('0' + j) : ('a' + j - offset);
+        tmp += (i >= offset) ? ('a' + j - offset) : ('0' + j);
     }
     tmp += ".ohos";
